# Conventions

## Project Context

This is a public SDK consumed by external users. Treat exported symbols as public contracts.

## Public API Stability

- Do not introduce breaking API changes without a deprecation and migration path.
- Additive changes are preferred over removals or signature changes.
- Check backwards compatibility before finalizing edits.

## Toolchain and Commands

- Package manager: `npm`
- Typecheck: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Lint: `ESLint` (typescript-eslint strict config)
- Format: `Prettier` (see `.prettierrc.json`)
- Task runner: `just` (see `.justfile`)
- Common commands: `just setup`, `just check`, `just test`, `just tidy`

## Git Workflow

- Use Conventional Commits: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Allowed types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `style`, `perf`
- Use branch names like `<type>/<change-slug>` (optionally with issue number)

## Worktree Expectations

- Use a dedicated worktree per agent session in `.worktrees/`.
- Create from `origin/main`: `git worktree add .worktrees/<name> -b <branch-name> origin/main`
- Remove after merge: `git worktree remove .worktrees/<name>`
- Announce the worktree name when creating or switching.

## Import Convention

TypeScript imports must use `.js` extensions for local module imports in emitted npm packages.

- Correct: `import { Thing } from './thing.js';`
- Incorrect: `import { Thing } from './thing.ts';`
- Incorrect: `import { Thing } from './thing';`

## Testing Process

For TypeScript implementation and test edits, follow the strict TDD rule in `tdd.mdc`.

## Agent rules (Cursor)

Additional always-on rules in `.cursor/rules/`: `security.mdc` (secrets, non-public surfaces, dependencies, workflows), `oss.mdc` (README quality, tests and docs hygiene, LICENSE/CONTRIBUTING). See `.claude/CLAUDE.md` for the full Claude Code narrative.
